'''Chad Hilse''' was an [[Alderaanian/Legends|Alderaanian]] [[Ensign/Legends|ensign]] in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. Dedicated to defeating the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], he was serving aboard the [[CR90 corvette/Legends|CR90 corvette]] [[Tantive IV/Legends|''Tantive IV'']] when it was [[Battle of Tatooine (Galactic Civil War)|attacked]] and disabled by the [[Imperial I-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial I''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Devastator/Legends|''Devastator'']]. While protecting [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] and the captured [[Death Star plans/Legends|Death Star plans]] she possessed, Hilse [[Death/Legends|died]] when trying to defend the [[Starship/Legends|ship]] from the [[501st Legion/Legends|501st Legion]] [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] unit.

==Biography==
Chad Hilse was a [[Human/Legends|Human]]<ref name="ANH" /> from the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]]. During the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]], he<ref name="SWE" /> became a [[Rebel Marine|marine]]<ref name="TCG" /> and volunteer [[Rebel trooper/Legends|trooper]] for the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]], attaining the rank of [[Ensign/Legends|ensign]] and receiving training in both [[Space warfare/Legends|starship]] and [[Ground warfare/Legends|ground]] combat.<ref name="SWE" /> In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]],<ref name="NEC" /> he was stationed aboard the [[CR90 corvette/Legends|CR90 corvette]] [[Tantive IV/Legends|''Tantive IV'']] when [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] received a transmission from Rebel [[Spy/Legends|spies]] containing [[Death Star plans/Legends|plans]] for the [[Death Star/Legends|Death Star]], a massive [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Battle station/Legends|battle station]] and [[Superweapon/Legends|superweapon]].<ref name="ANH" />

Hilse was aboard the ''Tantive IV'' when it was [[Battle of Tatooine (Galactic Civil War)|attacked]] and disabled over [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] by the [[Imperial I-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial I''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Devastator/Legends|''Devastator'']], the [[Flagship/Legends|flagship]] of the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]].<ref name="ANH" /> After taking defensive positions along the corvette's corridors, Hilse and his fellow [[Soldier/Legends|soldiers]] engaged the [[501st Legion/Legends|501st Legion]] [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtrooper]] unit.<ref name="Star Wars: Battlefront II">''[[Star Wars: Battlefront II]]''</ref> He was among the first to [[Death/Legends|die]]<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|II|42|Hilse, Chad}}</ref> in the ensuing gunfight.<ref name="ANH" />

==Personality and traits==
Chad Hilse typified the loyal Rebel volunteers dedicated to defeating the Empire.<ref name="CCG">{{CCG|set=Premiere Limited|cardname=Rebel Trooper}}</ref> He had light skin,<ref name="ANH" /> [[Color/Legends|brown]] [[Hair/Legends|hair]],<ref name="Toy1" /> and blue [[Eye/Legends|eyes]].<ref name="Toy3" />

==Equipment==
During his service on the ''Tantive IV'', Chad Hilse wore<ref name="ANH" /> the standard [[Alliance Fleet trooper uniform|uniform]] for [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]] [[Trooper/Legends|troopers]].<ref name="Rebel Alliance Sourcebook">[[The Rebel Alliance Sourcebook (Second Edition)|''The Rebel Alliance Sourcebook'', Second Edition]] includes a depiction of the standard [[Alliance Fleet/Legends|Alliance Fleet]] [[Rebel trooper/Legends|trooper]] uniforms, which matches the outfit worn by Chad Hilse.</ref> He was armed with a [[DH-17 blaster pistol/Legends|DH-17 blaster pistol]].<ref name="ANH" /> Hilse wore a [[Hat/Legends|cap]] as part of his uniform, and his equipment also included a [[Bandolier/Legends|bandolier]] and a [[Security scanner/Legends|scanner]].<ref name="Toy3" />

==Behind the scenes==
Chad Hilse appeared in the [[1977]] [[original trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']]. He was played by an uncredited extra,<ref name="ANH" /> whose scenes were filmed in mid [[1976]] in the [[Wikipedia:United Kingdom|United Kingdom]].<ref name="TMOSW">''[[The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film]]''</ref> The character had no lines<ref name="ANH" /> and was not identified by the name Chad Hilse until [[1995]] with the release of [[Decipher]]'s [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]]. His name and most of his backstory were featured on the "Rebel [[Troop/Legends|trooper]]" card in the ''[[Premiere Limited]]'' card set.<ref name="CCG" />

